7. **Clever Worldbuilding Feature:** In this city, every café is a memory vault—; the baristas are echoes of the past;  
8. **Scene:** Lila hands the cup—; the man’s eyes go black—*?!*  
9. **Punctuation:** “I don’t remember,” she said—; the cup cracked.  
10. **Semicolon:** The coffee spilled—; the floor became a mirror.  
11. **Colon:** She had one last thought: *I’m not real—; I’m a dream.*  
12. **Dash:** She didn’t scream—; she smiled.  
13. **Parentheses:** (The man was her father—; he never left.)  
14. **Ellipsis:** “I… I just wanted… to be seen…”  
